A tiny JIT compiler that lowers Exo scheduling-language
kernels through xDSL (Python-native MLIR) to native code
via llvmlite's MCJIT, entirely in-process with no C
compilation step.

usage:

    $ uv run xdsl-exo examples/demo.py --mlir
    $ uv run xdsl-exo examples/demo.py --asm
    $ uv run xdsl-exo examples/demo.py --c
    $ uv run python examples/demo.py

how it works:

      Exo Python source
          v
      Exo LoopIR
          v
    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  xDSL
      MLIR module
          v
      MLIR LLVM dialect
          v
    - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - llvmlite
      Native code

references:

- https://github.com/xdslproject/xdsl/blob/main/README.md
- https://github.com/exo-lang/exo/blob/main/docs/README.md
- https://github.com/kaylendog/exo-mlir
